OL,3,C'They were less than human': Britain's
OL,4,Cforced adoption scandal
OL,6,F"There was an anti Irish migrant
OL,7,Frhetoric and the cost to the British
OL,8,Ftaxpayer is something that comes up a
OL,9,Flot in the archives," she said.
OL,11,F"They were justifying it about the
OL,12,Fcost. It was a real culture of shame,
OL,13,Fsecrecy and oppression."
OL,15,FAfter spending two years at
OL,16,FCastlepollard mother and baby Home in
OL,17,FCounty Westmeath, Ireland, which at
OL,18,Ftime had a 40% infant mortality rate,
OL,19,FMaria was adopted by a woman who she
OL,20,Fdescribed as "emotionally abusive".
